I follow {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.advancedfictionwriting.com/articles/snowflake-method/"}}{\fldrslt Snowflake}}, and have adapted it somewhat for series development. This section links the steps to the location for each step.\
Throughout the steps that follow, I offer where the data should be kept in Scrivener. This approach seeks to leverage the strengths of Scrivener.\
For example, the Series Treatment comprises the one-page Story Summaries. The Story Synopses are in the Story Summary\'92s Inspector, and the Title of the Synopsis includes both the book title and the Story Logline. When you have Series Treatment selected in the Outliner, you\'92ll see the story taglines and synopses. When they are all selected and viewed in the editor, then you have a clean reading of the entire series.\
\
